channel.title: [teamview] server ip [teamview]
channel.description:
COULD SOMEONE VERY SKILLED WITH SERVERS PLEASE TEAMVIEW ME AND PLESE FIX MY SERVER ASAP.
OK, so im really ticked cause ive been trying to get this server up literally 5-8hrs a day for about 5 days now lol, nice life, right? na i got nights to kick it with my friends and go party, i got a life.
anyways, i got my port 43594 open on udp and tcp which can be confirmed through my port checker i dled from portforward.com
my server ip. when i put my ip from ipconfig from cmd, i can log in when i put it there, my friends can also get to the log-in part, but cant get through
when i put my ip from whatismyip.com, i cant log in it says error connecting to server and my friends get 1/4 through the dl to log in screen where it stops at cache.
i need help apparently. :confused: :confused: :confused: :confused: ill seriously do anything non money wise.

item.description:
@00mike wrote:

[quote=“WaleedScape, post:5, topic:338725”]Actually, I had this same problem, but solved it.
OK, so, u wont use a NORMAL IP, you should use NO-IP
because, u can update ur no-ip every time ur ip has changed
however, if u have a regular ip, (e.g 567.5345) then, the ip changes, u have to renew it, and ppl have to dl a new client
so, get a no-ip ASAP to keep ur server on without going through shit
hope i helped :D[/quote]

I got static, but I tried that anyways and was no help.
Thanks for trying though.

item.title: [teamview] server ip [teamview]
item.dc:creator: @WaleedScape WaleedScape
item.description:
@WaleedScape wrote:

Actually, I had this same problem, but solved it.
OK, so, u wont use a NORMAL IP, you should use NO-IP
because, u can update ur no-ip every time ur ip has changed
however, if u have a regular ip, (e.g 567.5345) then, the ip changes, u have to renew it, and ppl have to dl a new client
so, get a no-ip ASAP to keep ur server on without going through shit
hope i helped
